transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, this is Kenneth Peters. I had recently, as of today, received an order.

Speaker 1: It was supposed to be the Viagra AGB, which is what you guys advertise.

Speaker 2: Uh-huh.

Speaker 1: And I got sent some generic something.

Speaker 2: Okay, I can help you.

Speaker 1: So I was trying to figure out what happened.

Speaker 2: I'll help you out here. I need your zip code.

Speaker 1: 28713.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: So we do sell both regular generic and the AGB,

Speaker 2: so there's a chance that there was a mix-up somewhere in the filling process, and that's what happened.

Speaker 1: If you got the regular, it is still a safe product, but we will get you the right thing no matter what.

Speaker 2: Are you on 81 Second Street Road?

Speaker 1: I am.

Speaker 2: What I received was the Sildenafil secret ingredient.

Speaker 1: Well, even the AGB is Sildenafil.

Speaker 2: That's the active ingredient in any Viagra, but it's the inactive stuff that makes the AGB different.

Speaker 1: But what can confirm it for me is if you could take out a single pill and tell me what you see stamped on the pill.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Standby.

Speaker 1: Hang on. I'm on the phone.

Speaker 2: There's AC333.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, so you got the wrong one.

Speaker 2: Yours would have said 50, just 50, so I'm going to get you 20 of the right ones, sir.

Speaker 1: Like I said, those are safe, so if you want them as a backup plan, you can keep them, but you can also toss them if you want.

Speaker 2: I'm just going to get the pharmacy to send you out 20 of the right ones.

Speaker 1: Okay, of the actual AGBs, right?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir, of the actual AGBs.

Speaker 1: It's not going to cost you anything. You've already been charged.

Speaker 2: So I'm putting it through as a $0 transaction, so you'll get shipping emailed to you, but it's not going to actually charge you.

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds great. I appreciate your help.

Speaker 2: Do you happen to know how much money would be worth if they come in? We've got a trip coming up, that's why I'm asking.

Speaker 1: I'll ask them to do priority to get it out to you sooner.

Speaker 2: Awesome. I appreciate you. Thanks so much.

Speaker 1: Of course, sir. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: You too. Take care.

Speaker 1: Bye.
